281
00:15:41,336 --> 00:15:42,130
It's nothing.

282
00:15:42,527 --> 00:15:45,828
<i>Today's communique was conveniently
housed within an envelope.</i>

283
00:15:45,853 --> 00:15:48,455
<i>I found it in my shoe locker just like the note yesterday.</i>

284
00:15:48,622 --> 00:15:52,307
<i>I mean, seriously, is putting notes
in people's shoe locker some new trend?</i>

285
00:15:52,713 --> 00:15:55,744
<i>Well, thing is, this time around, it's different.</i>

286
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:02,733
<i>I have to be careful. I don't wanna waltz in
there just to face another life or death situation.</i>

287
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:05,864
<i>It doesn't matter, though, 'cause I'm going anyway.</i>

288
00:16:06,070 --> 00:16:09,034
<i>I mean, Miss Asahina wanted to see me in private.</i>

289
00:16:09,407 --> 00:16:15,041
<i>Now, I don't have any proof that Miss Asahina actually
sent this letter, but I know in my gut that she did, okay?</i>

290
00:16:15,255 --> 00:16:18,108
<i>She's definitely the type that
would send little notes to people,</i>

291
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:23,178
<i>and the image I'm seeing of her scribbling away on
super-cute stationary fits her personality to a T.</i>

292
00:16:23,354 --> 00:16:26,688
<i>Besides, it's the clubroom. Nagato's gonna be there.</i>

293
00:16:26,966 --> 00:16:28,640
<i>Well, here goes nothing.</i>

294
00:16:30,153 --> 00:16:31,717
Ah, come in!

295
00:16:33,999 --> 00:16:34,991
Hi, Kyon.

296
00:16:36,169 --> 00:16:37,692
It's been ages.

297
00:16:38,605 --> 00:16:40,584
<i>She sure looks like Miss Asahina,</i>

298
00:16:41,044 --> 00:16:43,361
<i>but she definitely is not Miss Asahina.</i>

299
00:16:44,498 --> 00:16:47,200
